info.title: AeroDataBox
info.description: Enthusiast-driven aviation and flight data API for a small travel or aviation application. Flight status, delays, schedules. Airports, runways, delay index, statistics, distance and flight-time between. Aircraft information, aircraft image recognition by registration.

parameters.name: icao
parameters.description: 4-digit ICAO-code of the airport (e.g.: EHAM, KLAX, UUEE, etc.). Full, stripped and any case formats are acceptable.

get.operationId: Airport data feed services status by ICAO code
get.description: Gets current status of airport data feed services (live flight updates, flight schedules, etc.) for requested airport.

parameters.name: service

get.description:

parameters.description: Should include aircraft image.

parameters.name: withLocation
parameters.description: Should include real-time positional data, e.g.: location, speed, altitude, etc., if available

parameters.name: searchParameter
searchBy

get.description:
Gets information about the status of the nearest (either in past or in future) flight or about flight departing or arriving on the day specified (local time), operated:
- under specified flight number; or
- by an aircraft with specified registration; or
- under specified ATC-callsign; or
- by an aircraft with specified Mode-S 24-bit ICAO Transponder address.

parameters.name: toLocal
parameters.description: End of the search range (local time, format: YYYY-MM-DD)

parameters.name: fromLocal
parameters.description: Beginning of the search range (local time, format: YYYY-MM-DD)

parameters.name: searchParameter
searchBy

get.description:
**On which days the flight operates?** or **What is the flight schedule?**

Get flight departure dates for a flight operated:
, operated:
- under specified flight number; or
- by an aircraft with specified registration; or
- under specified ATC-callsign; or
- by an aircraft with specified Mode-S 24-bit ICAO Transponder address.

Returns: Array of local departure dates in (YYYY-MM-DD).

parameters.name: searchParam

get.operationId: Aircraft by reg. / hex ICAO 24-bit address
get.description: Returns: Single aircraft data, if found

parameters.name: withPrivate
parameters.description: If set to true, result will include private flights (subject to availability).

parameters.name: withLeg
parameters.description: If set to true, will include movement information from airport opposite in this flight leg (airport of origin for arriving flight or airport of destination for departing flight). In this case, Movement property will be replaced with Departure and Arrival properties for each flight. Default: false.

parameters.name: withCodeshared
parameters.description: If set to true, result will include flights with all code-shared statuses. Otherwise, code-sharing flights will be excluded. For airports, where no information about code-share statuses of flights are supplied (all flights are CodeshareStatus=Unknown), complex filtering will be applied to determine which flights are likely to be operational (caution: false results are possible).

parameters.name: withCancelled
parameters.description: If set to true, result will include cancelled, divered, likely cancelled (CanceledUncertain) flights. Default: true.

parameters.name: withCargo
parameters.description: If set to true, result will include cargo flights (subject to availability).

parameters.name: direction
parameters.description: Direction of flights: Arrival, Departure or Both (default)

parameters.name: toLocal
parameters.description: End of the search range (local time, format: YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm). Should be more than beginning of the search range, but not more than by 12 hours.

parameters.name: fromLocal
parameters.description: Beginning of the search range (local time, format: YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm)

parameters.name: icao
parameters.description: 4-digit ICAO-code of the airport (e.g.: EHAM, KLAX, UUEE, etc.). Full, stripped and any case formats are acceptable.

get.operationId: Departures and arrivals (FIDS) by airport ICAO code
get.description:
**What are current departures or arrivals at the airport? **or **What is the flight schedule at the airport?** or **What is flight history at the airport?**

Information with live updates and actual arrival/departure times is only available for airports tracked live by our system. Otherwise flight information will be with scheduled info only or absent. To check if airport is tracked and on which level, use /health/services/airports/{icao}/feeds endpoint. You can also use /health/services/feeds/{service}/airports to get the list of supported airports.

Returns: information about departing and arriving flights within specified time range for the specified airport.

parameters.name: withFlightInfoOnly
parameters.description: If set to true, will only return airports which have flight data (scheduled or live) available. Default = false.

post.description:
**What aircrafts are depicted on this photo?**

This endpoint recognizes aircrafts on uploaded image and returns information about all detected aircrafts. It is based on computer vision technology and therefore results may be imprecise. It relies on detecting aircrafts' registrations and, once detected, attempting to match these registration with records in aircrafts database.

Returns: Data about found and recognized aircrafts.

photo.description: Image containing aircraft. It should be image-type file (JPEG, PNG or BMP).  To improve results:  ensure that aircraft registration is as much as possible visible on the image; other inscriptions are visible as least as possible or absent on the image (although algorithm strives to filter these out as much as possible, false results are still possible).

parameters.name: reg
parameters.description: Registration of the aircraft (full, stripped and any case formats are acceptable).

get.description:
**What is the aircraft photo?  **

Aircraft images are being searched externally in Flickr. Only images with licenses approved for commercial use are returned. Please be advised that you may be required to mention author attribution before using the image.  

Returns: Image data with medium-sized direct image URL and licence approved for commercial use is returned.
